  <span id="freeText6037827072306172896" style="display:none"><br />This was a reread for me. It didn't quite thrill me as much as it did the first time I read it but I still think it rates a 5.<br /><br />I love Mary Stewarts take on the Arthurian tale in this series, especially this opening book where she she begins with Merlin as a child and draws out the history through him. Stewart has taken some liberties and added her own special twist to the story which, to me, brings a unique viewpoint to the legend. <br /><br />Enter the pages of this series and discover the true creator of Stonehenge. ;)</span>
