    <a title="Samantha" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/30749549-samantha"><img alt="Samantha" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1541655277p2/30749549.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1452257282?book_show_action=true">Nov 25, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Samantha" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Samantha" href="/user/show/30749549-samantha">Samantha</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780449911617" href="/book/show/813021.The_Crystal_Cave">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1452257282" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer342774038594549475">3.5/5 Yay! I finally finished a book! <br/>The crystal cave is the first in an Arthurian retelling saga. Told from the perspective of Merlin, it follows him from a young boy to a young man in his late teens/early twenties.<br/>Overall, I really enjoyed it! I love how she incorporated so many different elements from the original legends while still making them new. <br/>I think my biggest complaint was lack of character development. Even Merlin didn&apos;t feel very developed and he was the one telling the story! It</span>
  <span id="freeText342774038594549475" style="display:none">3.5/5 Yay! I finally finished a book! <br />The crystal cave is the first in an Arthurian retelling saga. Told from the perspective of Merlin, it follows him from a young boy to a young man in his late teens/early twenties.<br />Overall, I really enjoyed it! I love how she incorporated so many different elements from the original legends while still making them new. <br />I think my biggest complaint was lack of character development. Even Merlin didn't feel very developed and he was the one telling the story! It just all seemed a bit flat and any scenes in which action occurred was glossed over. It also all felt a bit anti-climatic....not a whole lot went on and big events where skipped over with simple summary lines like, well this happened, and now everything changed in this way.<br />I really did enjoy the story however, Stewart's writing was excellent and I'm intrigued enough to continue on!</span>
  <a data-text-id="342774038594549475" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
